            <p>The getHeader() method returns the header field as it appears in the original mail message.</p>

<p>This should be in one of two formats: "email@domain.com" or "Joe Bloggs <a href="mailto:email@domain.com">email@domain.com</a>".</p>

<p>If you directly output the latter (name ) as HTML, the email address won't be visible since browsers interpret it as a tag.</p>

<p>In short, not a bug.</p>

